<br><br>
<em>Figure 7: European land surface temperature: annual anomalies with the current year in green. The grey bands show the uncertainty in the averaged temperature (left). Daily anomalies with respect to the seasonal cycle until the end of September 2017 (right).</em>
<br><br>
<h3>Precipitation</h3>
<br><br>
September has been exceptionally dry over Spain, Portugal and southwest France where the dry conditions of the 2017 summer are continued (left panels of Figure 8 and Figure 9). Other areas in southern Europe, like Italy and the Balkans, have seen wetter than average conditions in September. Parts of northern France, the Alps and the area shared by Finland and northwestern Russia have seen some days with heavy precipitation, where both the maximum one-day precipitation sum and the maximum precipitation for 5 consecutive days has been in the top 10% of events (centre and right panels of Figure 8 and Figure 9).
